                  <h3 class="text-center">Maze</h3>
                  <div class="row game-slide" id="maze">
                    <div class="small-6 columns" >
                      <img src="/assets/home/maze.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="small-4 columns">
                      <p>This game is like the regular maze game, where the player is asked to go through a maze to reach his/her goal. What’s different in this game is the presence of some obstacles along the way, these obstacles are represented as MCQs. The player will listen to the arabic words, and chooses the corresponding letter. In order to pass the obstacle, the corresponding question has to be answered correctly.
The deficit Area it handles :  Auditory Deficit.</p>
                      <a id="mazeGame" class="large button sites-button hide-for-small-only">Play Game</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="orbit-slide">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-center">Flipping Cards</h3>
                  <div class="row game-slide" id="flippingCards">
                    <div class="small-6 columns" >
                      <img src=" /assets/home/matching.png"/>

                    </div>
                    <div class="small-4 columns">
                      <p>This game is like the regular memory flipping card game, where the player is asked to match two identical cards that are flipped down on the table after seeking the whole thing for a short span of time.
The deficit Area it handles :  Memory Deficit.</p>
                      <a id="flippingGame" class="large button sites-button hide-for-small-only">Play Game</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="orbit-slide">
