                    </div>
                    <div class="small-4 columns">
                      <p>This game’s idea is to shoot the correct group of words/images that belong to a certain group. (Ex: Shoot all the words that starts with the letter “Alef”).
The deficit Area it handles :  Attention Deficit.</p>
                      <a id="shootingGame" class="large button sites-button hide-for-small-only">Play Game</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="orbit-slide">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-center">Hangman</h3>
                  <div class="row game-slide" id="hangman">
                    <div class="small-6 columns" >
                      <img src="/assets/home/hangman.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="small-4 columns">
                      <p> This game is a typical normal Hangman game where the child is asked to fill in the gaps of the missing letters of a certain word.
 The deficit Area it handles :  Language Deficit.</p>
                      <a id="hangmanGame" class="large button sites-button hide-for-small-only">Play Game</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="orbit-slide">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-center">Puzzle</h3>
                  <div class="row game-slide" id="puzzle">
                    <div class="small-6 columns" >
                      <img src="/assets/home/puzzle.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="small-4 columns">
                      <p>This game is a puzzle game where the child gets to reorganize the scattered parts of the letter’s image along with the images of the objects that start with this letter. But, exceptionally, the student has first to pick the correct image that he/she will be required to solve as a puzzle. This will come along 
P.S: All the puzzle challenges come with a preview image as an examples.
The deficit Area it handles :  Organizational Deficit.</p>
                      <a id="puzzleGame"class="large button sites-button hide-for-small-only">Play Game</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="orbit-slide">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-center">Drag and Drop</h3>
                  <div class="row game-slide" id="draganddrop">
                    <div class="small-6 columns" >
                      <img src="/assets/home/drag.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="small-4 columns">
                      <p> The classical matching game using drag and drop method, we will have a set of empty cards written on them the arabic words or letters, and below them a collection of images where the child is required to drag and drop it in the right slot.
The deficit Area it handles : Visual Deficit.</p>
                      <a id="dragGame" class="large button sites-button hide-for-small-only">Play Game</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="orbit-slide">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-center">Letter Paint</h3>
                  <div class="row game-slide" id="letterpaint">
                    <div class="small-6 columns" >
                      <img src="/assets/home/writing.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="small-4 columns">
                      <p>This game stresses on the writing skills of the child by having the arabic letter on the screen and asking the child to color/fill it with his/her finger, under the condition that they don’t go outside the letter nor color a small part of it.
The deficit Area it handles :  Writing Deficit.</p>
                      <a id="letterpaintGame" class="large button sites-button hide-for-small-only">Play Game</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
   
